00:29:04.220 --> 00:29:06.405
I mean, you've got the
place set up for efficiency.

00:29:06.405 --> 00:29:07.030
BILL KIM: Yeah.

00:29:07.030 --> 00:29:10.210
So we just held a smart
class this morning.

00:29:10.210 --> 00:29:13.510
So it's our second time around.

00:29:13.510 --> 00:29:16.240
We try to bring technology
into our kitchen,

00:29:16.240 --> 00:29:21.070
so we are Wi-Fi and
Bluetooth connected

00:29:21.070 --> 00:29:23.440
in our kitchen, which is crazy.

00:29:23.440 --> 00:29:27.550
So I could see on my phone if
somebody's using the oven right

00:29:27.550 --> 00:29:29.830
now, at what temperature.

00:29:29.830 --> 00:29:30.505
And now--

00:29:30.505 --> 00:29:32.380
CHANGDRA RAM: Now you're
the creepy overlord.

00:29:32.380 --> 00:29:33.004
BILL KIM: Yeah.

00:29:33.004 --> 00:29:40.630
And with the phone,
and also, now,

00:29:40.630 --> 00:29:46.030
with Wi-Fi built into the
ovens, so basically now,

00:29:46.030 --> 00:29:48.340
we download the picture
of the finished product.

00:29:48.340 --> 00:29:51.640
Let's say you're charring
broccoli in the oven.

00:29:51.640 --> 00:29:56.140
So now, they have ovens
where you could put dry heat

00:29:56.140 --> 00:29:58.070
and humidity at the same time.

00:29:58.070 --> 00:30:02.980
So you could do
70% dry, 30% steam.

00:30:02.980 --> 00:30:04.510
And you could cook in there.

00:30:04.510 --> 00:30:06.490
And basically, the
finished product comes out.

00:30:06.490 --> 00:30:10.630
We take a picture,
download that to the oven.

00:30:10.630 --> 00:30:16.150
And now a prep cook that just
starts, they just have to say,

00:30:16.150 --> 00:30:18.730
"Broccoli," show a picture.

00:30:18.730 --> 00:30:21.250
Now you don't need to remember
temperatures or settings.

00:30:21.250 --> 00:30:25.990
Now, you just press the
picture of the broccoli.

00:30:25.990 --> 00:30:29.830
You could also, if you're taking
something out of the freezer,

00:30:29.830 --> 00:30:32.560
let's say, and you
put it into this--

00:30:32.560 --> 00:30:33.940
it's called the blast chiller.

00:30:33.940 --> 00:30:38.530
Take it, set it
on thaw overnight.

00:30:38.530 --> 00:30:40.900
And you don't have to run water.

00:30:40.900 --> 00:30:43.570
You're wasting water,
wasting energy.

00:30:43.570 --> 00:30:46.610
And basically, when
you come the next day,

00:30:46.610 --> 00:30:48.340
you take it from
the frozen stage.

00:30:48.340 --> 00:30:50.800
Then it thaws it out,
and you're ready to go.

00:30:50.800 --> 00:30:52.950
So you're not wasting time.

00:30:52.950 --> 00:30:55.570
You could also what's
called "proofing."

00:30:55.570 --> 00:30:58.350
You could actually make bread.

00:30:58.350 --> 00:31:01.520
Then you could shock-freeze
it at negative 40.

00:31:01.520 --> 00:31:05.280
So it doesn't kill the
yeast, but it freezes it.

00:31:05.280 --> 00:31:07.870
Then two days later,
you could take it out

00:31:07.870 --> 00:31:13.600
before you go home, let it proof
very slowly, relax the dough.

00:31:13.600 --> 00:31:17.400
So a person coming the next
day could actually take it

00:31:17.400 --> 00:31:18.400
as soon as they come in.

00:31:18.400 --> 00:31:21.790
They could bake off the bread,
which sometimes could take up

00:31:21.790 --> 00:31:25.730
to two or three hours in a
busy kitchen, to take up space.

00:31:25.730 --> 00:31:28.960
So there's also a
controlled vapor cooking,

00:31:28.960 --> 00:31:34.780
which is basically, if you're
making grits or polenta,

00:31:34.780 --> 00:31:38.180
there's a point where
when you're cooking it,

00:31:38.180 --> 00:31:41.680
it has this like splatter
thing that happens.

00:31:41.680 --> 00:31:46.460
And it's like almost
getting hit with heat.

00:31:46.460 --> 00:31:49.540
You almost need a visor,
like a welding helmet,

00:31:49.540 --> 00:31:51.940
because the things
just kind of bubble.

00:31:51.940 --> 00:31:55.030
So this controlled
vapor cooking,

00:31:55.030 --> 00:31:56.680
you just bring it up to a boil.

00:31:56.680 --> 00:31:57.580
Then you cover it.

00:31:57.580 --> 00:32:01.870
Just put it in
basically an oven.

00:32:01.870 --> 00:32:03.640
It's controlled
atmosphere of cooking.

00:32:03.640 --> 00:32:06.610
Two hours later, it's
completely cooked.

00:32:06.610 --> 00:32:10.570
So what it does is first,
it gives the person

00:32:10.570 --> 00:32:12.910
that's actually
cooking it complete

00:32:12.910 --> 00:32:14.230
control of the product.

00:32:14.230 --> 00:32:19.040
And also, it gives that person
time to do other things.

00:32:19.040 --> 00:32:21.470
So you don't have to
keep an eye on things.

00:32:21.470 --> 00:32:24.880
It's like the Instapot,
everybody is going--

00:32:24.880 --> 00:32:28.360
so we have an Instapot
kind of thing,

00:32:28.360 --> 00:32:32.410
where if you have a braised
short rib that you want to do,

00:32:32.410 --> 00:32:36.670
we could put it in before we
go home, next morning come,

00:32:36.670 --> 00:32:38.560
and hold it at the
same temperature.

00:32:38.560 --> 00:32:40.060
It's completely cooked.

00:32:40.060 --> 00:32:45.070
So there's the efficiency of us
cooking while we're not there.

00:32:45.070 --> 00:32:46.810
And it's not by heat.

00:32:46.810 --> 00:32:48.840
It's by electricity.

00:32:48.840 --> 00:32:54.050
And it's controlled
100%, and it's done.

00:32:54.050 --> 00:32:56.530
And what that does
is I can hire people

00:32:56.530 --> 00:33:01.120
that need a career out of it.

00:33:01.120 --> 00:33:02.470
They don't need to be chefs.

00:33:02.470 --> 00:33:04.210
They just need a job.

00:33:04.210 --> 00:33:06.520
And we have people
who want a job.

00:33:06.520 --> 00:33:08.680
They want to go home
at a certain time.

00:33:08.680 --> 00:33:09.380
They have kids.

00:33:09.380 --> 00:33:10.960
They have other responsibility.

00:33:10.960 --> 00:33:15.310
Now we can teach them a skill
that they could provide us.

00:33:15.310 --> 00:33:18.510
Because not everybody
is aspiring to be chefs.

00:33:18.510 --> 00:33:21.280
And we could give people
a chance that might not

00:33:21.280 --> 00:33:23.270
have a chance in life.

00:33:23.270 --> 00:33:26.590
So these are things
that we put in place

00:33:26.590 --> 00:33:29.099
so we could hire more people.

